Given the following dataframe, you intend to draw a bar chart with category (x-axis) and count (y-axis), using `ggplot()`. Which of the following command would give the correct bar chart? [see_image_1] #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:21042021033053] https://t.co/GMeMgzLkfQ

But in our example, we already have the count, so we need to use `stat='identity'`, which leaves the data unchanged. [see_image_1] #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:21042021163031] https://t.co/m8YCeVitOJ

Correct Option: `ggplot(tble, aes(x=category, y=count)) + geom_bar(stat='identity')`. The default behaviour of `geom_bar()` automatically counts value and requires only x aesthetic i.e. `ggplot(tble, aes(x=category)) + geom_bar()`. #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:21042021163031] https://t.co/bqRU7C2Dzt
